    <svcsection id="s05009t" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5072T" revno="T" date="02/10/1997">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>05710</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The steering column assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0500901">Figure 1</hotlnk>) provides the vehicle operator control of the steering
                    gear from inside the vehicle cab. Operators also have the capability to tilt and/or telescope the
                    steering column to their own driving needs.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0500901" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0500901" filename="../figg05/G0500901.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Tilt/Telescope Steering Column Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. STEERING GEAR END YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. UNIVERSAL JOINT</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. LOWER END YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. END YOKE PINCH BOLT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. UNIVERSAL JOINT SHAFT</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. STEERING COLUMN END YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. HORN BUTTON</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. STEERING WHEEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. COVER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>11. SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>12. PLATE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>13. BOTTOM COVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>14. STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>15. TOP COVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>16. COLUMN BRACKETS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>A steering wheel is connected to the upper steering shaft. The steering shaft is connected to the
                    slip shaft by a universal joint. The lower end of the slip shaft is connected to the steering gear
                    by a second universal joint. The universal joints and slip shaft permit correct alignment and smooth
                    rotation of the steering shaft to steering gear with no binding of the shafts.
                </para>
                <para>The turn signal and trailer brake controls are mounted to the steering column jacket tube.</para>
                <para>The horn will not operate with the ignition switch in the "OFF" position. When the ignition switch
                    is in the "ON" or "ACCESSORY" position, current is available at the horn relay. To energize the
                    relay and feed current to the horn, a path to ground is completed through the horn button mechanism
                    in the steering column.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
